message: React Hook "React.useContext" is called in function "getCMSContent" that is neither a React function component nor a custom React Hook function. React component names must start with an uppercase letter. React Hook names must start with the word "use".
The object passed as the value prop to the Context provider changes every render. To fix this consider wrapping it in a useMemo hook.

Do not define components during render. React will see a new component type on every render and destroy the entire subtree’s DOM nodes and state. Instead, move this component definition out of the parent component “FAQQuestionScreen” and pass data as props. If you want to allow component creation in props, set allowAsProps option to true.
Expected an assignment or function call and instead saw an expression.
Complete the task associated to this "TODO" comment.
